ce:section.ce:para:
The N-CQDs encapsulated within the KH-560 gel still maintain excellent luminescent properties, with a QY as high as 71.87 % for NK-10. Compared to previously reported solid-state blue luminescent CQDs, NK-10 exhibits high luminescent efficiency (Table 1
                        ). In Fig. 5
                        a, the CIE chromaticity charts for the maximum emission wavelengths of NK-10 and NK-25 are depicted, with coordinates of (0.16, 0.15) and (0.19, 0.30), respectively, confirming their blue and cyan luminescence. Fig. 5b shows LED lamps prepared by mixing NK-10 and NK-25 with transparent silicone, then dispensing them onto LED chips. When powered on, these LED lamps emit bright blue and cyan light individually. Fig. 5c displays images of the letters “A" and “B" drawn on paper using NK-10 and NK-25. When exposed to ultraviolet excitation, they respectively exhibit a blue “A" and a cyan “B". These results indicate that NK powders can find applications in LED lighting and fluorescent ink.
